[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing Confluent issues**\n\nI'm looking into an interesting repo that can't seem to resolve Confluent. It seems the issue generator may use external setups and is excluding certain repositories, which could be a factor. I need to inspect the Confluent documentation, especially around the Avro serializer requirement for a Schema Registry URL. I wonder if the `mock://` pseudo-protocol can be utilized in their serializers. Tests might need to set a mock URL to avoid real Schema Registry interactions. It's intriguing to consider if any additional setup is necessary for robust coverage.\n\n**Examining Kafka serializer tests**\n\nI’m considering how tests compile for Kafka serializers. The `kafka-avro-serializer` references `org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.Serializer`, and if it's set as `compileOnly` in Gradle, then projects using `KafkaAvroSerializer` may need `kafka-clients` for testing. To figure this out, I should check how Gradle resolves dependencies with the Confluent repo. Since I’m facing issues with Maven Central, maybe I can use a downloaded Gradle wrapper to generate a temporary project for testing. It feels like a lot to keep track of!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e87ce5736d11310016a3b14316b348196a3186d1fbb68e54e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqOxQ6wcOlrk-mDLrfrp2yPar1d9qa90sN16RtIIV7Ycj0NdW6Cm-7jKgmiJRxUDpNT1SnYZYPdkdgTJ2e9U-exKP93xfB9f-gC4HA5nguQvCgWIVfsGAh5p9_78fTo0-S6hnvoa3qeV_tOJ_yl9Y2ubSyL4B_2VUtHQi5_oGnusRgTp-kgOgcjV4ZtFGk3aZJTwmK0CG9JHKNV-mGjJQDZ0FppIs4eH3lCYrrC-nkriKcrrNyxrIh1JfqsGBNPCRn-x7wppmKGmnglm8aSVbKqO0nVkBCI2OaqeP2HAWCPZn2n2C4h5t8N0GtvRFtxFeWyNx2seQDBqnIOxCeTda0TWvF1keFNLxu5KRm4hZnViHxUlX8jUIFrPteKO_WAn_eB4VkrzCqdwjIuq3Oo74lUi-P1FeHARbh0u5jQXTzmBC8SLCBCqLahDe1ANsALFEpcVqhVcMHtSR6j-ztf6m5hvSs9Hwj6SLVXl_p5BldqwHMi7f6aWRBjDU8FGOAsGZ8r1AxyrLIrH4qZnE1gI1pwN8A9HigmMxLvH0pD2u7Q8_HIuP